name="doi">10.48550/arXiv.2310.02051</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We walk through a few proofs of canonicity and normalization, each one with more aspects dissected and re-expressed in category theory, so that readers can compare the difference across proofs. During this process we isolate the different ideas that make up the proofs. Finally we arrive at <fr:link
href="sterling-2021-thesis.xml"
type="local"
addr="sterling-2021-thesis">synthetic Tait computability</fr:link> as proposed by <fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">J. Sterling</fr:link>. We also give a synthetic proof for parametricity of system F.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:contributions><fr:context></fr:context><fr:related></fr:related><fr:backlinks></fr:backlinks><fr:references></fr:references></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>